def plot_dist(x, figsize = (10, 10)):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = figsize)

    rows = 6
    cols = 3

    for i, t in enumerate(df['type'].unique()):
        fig.add_subplot(rows, cols, i+1)
        temp = df[df['type'] == t][x].dropna()
        sns.distplot(temp, kde = False).set_title(f'{t} {x} distribution')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
def plot_all(figsize = (10, 10)):
    # Price distribution according to type
    plot_dist('price_usd', figsize = figsize)
    
    # Rooms distribution
    fig = plt.figure(figsize = (12, 2))
    sns.distplot(df['rooms'].dropna(), kde = False).set_title('Rooms distribution')
    plt.show()

    # Area distribution
    plot_dist('area', figsize = figsize)

Outliers elimination¶

In [12]:
# Eliminating outliers using 1.5 IQR
print(f'Data shape before outlier elimination: {df.shape}')

cols = [col for col in df.columns if df[col].dtype == 'float64']

outliers = []

# Loop through all regions
for region in df['region'].unique():
    # Select observations that belong to distinct region
    region_df = df[df['region'] == region]
    
    # Loop through reql estate type
    for t in df['type'].unique():
        # Select observations of that type
        type_df = region_df[region_df['type'] == t]
        
        # Loop through numeric columns
        for col in cols:
            try:
                Q1 = type_df[col].quantile(0.25)
                Q3 = type_df[col].quantile(0.75)
                IQR = Q3 - Q1
                lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
                upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

                # DEBUG
            #     print(f'{col}:\nQ1 - {Q1}\nQ3 - {Q3}\nIQR - {IQR}\nlower_bound - {lower_bound}\nupper_bound - {upper_bound}\n')

                outliers.extend(type_df[type_df[col] < lower_bound][col].index.values)
                outliers.extend(type_df[type_df[col] > upper_bound][col].index.values)
            except:
                pass
    
outliers = set(outliers)

df.drop(outliers, inplace = True)

print(f'Data shape after outlier elimination: {df.shape}')

def split_string(x):       
    x = str(x)[::-1]       
    x = ' '.join([x[i:i+3] for i in range(0, len(x), 3)])[::-1]
    return x

f = folium.Figure()
m = folium.Map(location = [48.657403, 31.805420], zoom_start = 5.6)

with open('boundaries.json', encoding = 'utf-8') as f:
    geo = json.load(f)

for feature in geo['features']:    
    region = feature['properties']['Region']    
    value = region_value[region_value['region'] == region]['price_usd'].values
    if value:
        value = split_string(int(value[0]))       
        feature['properties']['Market value'] = value
    else:
        feature['properties']['Market value'] = 'No data'        
    
choro = folium.Choropleth(
    name = 'Region market value',
    geo_data = geo,
    data = region_value,
    columns = ['region', 'price_usd'],
    key_on = 'feature.properties.Region',
    fill_color = 'BuGn',
    highlight = True,
    legend_name = 'Market value',
    bins = 5,
    fill_opacity = 0.8,
    popup = 'test'
).add_to(m)

choro.geojson.add_child(folium.features.GeoJsonTooltip(
    fields = ['Region', 'Market value'],
    aliases = ['Region:', 'Market value (USD):'],
    localize = False,
    sticky = False,
    labels = True,    
    style="""
        background-color: #F0EFEF;
        border: 2px solid black;
        border-radius: 2px;
        box-shadow: 6px;
        """))

folium.LayerControl().add_to(m)
plugins.ScrollZoomToggler().add_to(m)
plugins.MiniMap().add_to(m)
    
m
